data.title: Annūr, Tamil Nādu, India
data.text:
Annūr is a town in the Coimbatore district of Tamil Nādu, India. It is located at 11.2333300 latitude and 77.1333300 longitude in the Asia/Kolkata timezone. The weather in Annūr is tropical, with hot summers and mild winters. The town has a rich history and heritage, dating back to the 10th century. It was once a major center of trade and commerce, and was home to many temples and mosques. Today, Annūr is a thriving town with a population of over 50,000 people.
